# [claude-code 2026-04-26] S45.5/F3: Piper voice weights live here.
#
# Expected files (committed via git-lfs per ../../.gitattributes):
#   en_GB-cori-medium.onnx
#   en_GB-cori-medium.onnx.json
#
# Source: https://huggingface.co/rhasspy/piper-voices/tree/main/en/en_GB/cori/medium
# Download both files (the .onnx is ~63MB) and drop them in this directory,
# then `git add` will route them through the LFS filter automatically.
#
# Until the weights are present:
#   - isPiperAvailable("cori") returns false
#   - synthesizeWithPiper returns null
#   - the voice router falls back to ElevenLabs ("Rachel" default)
#   - /api/voice/sample?voice=cori returns 503 synthesis_unavailable
#
# The Fly Docker image now COPYs this directory (see ../../Dockerfile);
# once weights land, redeploy backend-hono to pick them up. The Piper binary
# also needs to be installed in the container (apk add piper or equivalent) —
# tracked as a Dockerfile follow-up the first time TP wants Cori live.
